<br>
facts:<br>
<br>
Othmir Warriors have approx 5100 hp<br>
Othmir Shamans have approx  5800 to 6000 hp<br>
Othmir Chieftain is 100% MR but was single pullable with a dispell spell from max range.<br>
Othmir Shamans cast spells, and is therefore not adviced to be quadded.<br>
<br>
The 3 camps are called Vendor, Middle/chief, SS(skyshrine)<br>
<br>
Rumors state that othmirs cant be single pulled before lvl 57, I dont know about this since I didnt try before lvl 57 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Shamans seems to give twice the xp of a warrior, but it may be just my imagination.<br>
<br>
Aggro range is huge once you become KoS, but not as bad as raptors. All othmirs have sow speed, and I haven been able to dispell it. So I take it its an ability, snot spell on them.<br>
<br>
Once you become KoS gathering them is a pain, because casting AE snare directly at the spawn point usually means you get more in your snare then you want. The othmirs are closely packed. <br>
<br>
To get singles I use the lvl 16 lightning bolt spell, it has a 200 range so once it casted I have a shot at snaring the Othmir before he gets to me. I can get a single and snare him with a normal draught, but that only works if the camp is broken and the othmir is more or less alone, and I most often end up with the bugger beating on me before snare is applied.<br>
<br>
A wizard tactic Ive heard of but havent used is:<br>
Locate 4 warriors, run in and aggro them with the temp flux staff. Run out over the water (levitate) to slow them down and round them up, run in over the beach and pray that you manage to snare them all on first try otherwise gate ASAP.<br>
<br>
Lastly, I haven't tried to kill the vendors at North/vendor camp. But I think it would be a nig mistake. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131568" target="_blank">Belcarl</A>




 
 
 

